WEBVTT

00:11.594 --> 00:13.429
[mysterious music playing]

00:13.430 --> 00:14.806
[exhales]

00:22.772 --> 00:24.065
[exhales]

00:25.608 --> 00:27.819
- [intense action music playing]
- [grunting]

00:32.323 --> 00:34.993
[Mihawk] Weak as you ever were.

00:39.622 --> 00:40.832
[grunts]

00:46.504 --> 00:47.881
[inhales deeply]

00:49.507 --> 00:50.759
[exhales]

01:17.869 --> 01:19.871
[flamenco music playing]

01:20.497 --> 01:23.333
The distance between us remains chasmic.

01:25.668 --> 01:28.379
Keep up like this,
and you'll never reach me.

01:29.047 --> 01:30.255
[grunting]

01:30.256 --> 01:31.674
[intense action music playing]

01:42.811 --> 01:47.232
The waters of the Grand Line are
indeed too treacherous for a little frog.

01:48.942 --> 01:49.983
Fish, fish.

01:49.984 --> 01:51.401
- [mouthing]
- [Usopp] Big fish!

01:51.402 --> 01:53.112
Oh! She's huge!

01:53.113 --> 01:56.323
Get up here! [screams]

01:56.324 --> 01:57.241
[gasps]

01:57.242 --> 01:58.325
Hoo!

01:58.326 --> 02:01.286
She's biting! Oh man, this a monster!

02:01.287 --> 02:03.038
It might be a whale!

02:03.039 --> 02:05.666
Come on. Come on.

02:05.667 --> 02:06.750
Whoo!

02:06.751 --> 02:08.169
Oh. Whoo!

02:12.006 --> 02:14.508
Woo-hoo!

02:14.509 --> 02:17.261
No beast is a match for Captain Usopp!

02:17.262 --> 02:19.138
[swanky music playing]

02:19.139 --> 02:23.183
Ooh! See, this is what I'm talking about.

02:23.184 --> 02:26.270
Fish in the Grand Line are like
nothing you'd see in the East Blue.

02:26.271 --> 02:28.314
[Mr. 9] Spare me the indignity.

02:29.190 --> 02:33.235
I've been captured by a crew so provincial
they're impressed by a fish.

02:33.236 --> 02:34.611
We should gag him.

02:34.612 --> 02:36.614
[thunder rumbles]

02:38.950 --> 02:40.951
[Nami] This weather is crazy!

02:40.952 --> 02:44.247
It was warm and sunny a minute ago,
and now it's pouring rain.

02:44.831 --> 02:46.958
No wonder the Grand Line
is so hard to navigate.

02:50.295 --> 02:53.423
- [Sanji chuckles]
- Even the weather amazes you people.

02:54.215 --> 02:55.257
Ah.

02:55.258 --> 02:58.511
There's a special relationship
between a chef and his knives.

02:59.137 --> 03:01.848
Using them requires technique,

03:02.432 --> 03:03.600
talent,

03:05.268 --> 03:06.853
and style.

03:07.353 --> 03:10.898
That's the difference between us.
You cut things that are already dead.

03:10.899 --> 03:15.028
I already said the difference between us.
Technique, talent, and style.

03:18.573 --> 03:21.533
This weather defies all logic.

03:21.534 --> 03:23.952
The rain cleared up,
and now there's a blizzard.

03:23.953 --> 03:25.038
A blizzard!

03:32.420 --> 03:33.630
The Grand Line is insane.

03:35.465 --> 03:36.466
[door closes]

03:40.553 --> 03:42.304
Who wants to make a snowman?

03:42.305 --> 03:43.805
[Sanji] A snowman?

03:43.806 --> 03:45.350
I'm making sorbet!

03:46.184 --> 03:48.144
[Mr. 9 laughs]

03:49.229 --> 03:50.438
What's so funny?

03:51.022 --> 03:55.693
So this is what has become
of the great Roronoa Zoro.

03:56.361 --> 03:59.697
I can't believe
Baroque Works tried to recruit you.

04:00.365 --> 04:03.242
So you need a refresher
on what I did to Mr. 7, huh?

04:03.243 --> 04:04.409
[Mr. 9] Ooh.

04:04.410 --> 04:05.994
You think you can beat me?

04:05.995 --> 04:07.705
The cook beat you.

04:08.206 --> 04:09.873
So yeah, not really a question.

04:09.874 --> 04:12.919
You talk a hearty game
when your opponent can't fight back.

04:13.503 --> 04:17.006
Untie me, and let's see
how skilled you really are.

04:24.514 --> 04:25.932
Nice try.

04:35.483 --> 04:36.818
What's your name?

04:37.402 --> 04:38.735
Miss Wednesday.

04:38.736 --> 04:41.322
- That's a funny name.
- It's a code name.

04:41.906 --> 04:42.782
Oh.

04:46.244 --> 04:47.120
Well…

04:48.705 --> 04:49.664
[sighs]

04:54.752 --> 04:56.129
Do you like being an assassin?

04:56.713 --> 04:57.588
Adore it.

04:58.172 --> 04:59.173
Hmm.

05:02.635 --> 05:04.970
Why does your partner wear a crown?

05:04.971 --> 05:06.055
Childhood trauma.

05:06.556 --> 05:08.099
Okay. Hmm.

05:11.811 --> 05:13.688
Do you want something to eat?

05:14.230 --> 05:15.231
Uh…

05:16.107 --> 05:17.775
- What are you offering?
- Dried squid.

05:20.111 --> 05:21.446
Not mine though.

05:21.946 --> 05:23.613
- I'll get you some.
- [scoffs]

05:23.614 --> 05:24.741
No.

05:25.283 --> 05:28.243
Now, if you're done with
this inane excuse for an interrogation,

05:28.244 --> 05:30.496
I'd like to resume planning my escape.

05:32.373 --> 05:33.458
[Luffy sighs]

05:34.083 --> 05:35.960
I'm not interrogating you.

05:37.628 --> 05:39.339
I'm trying to get to know you.

05:43.634 --> 05:47.722
I'm a Baroque Works frontier agent.
That's all you need to know.

05:55.146 --> 05:56.230
Okay.

05:57.899 --> 05:59.316
[Nami] You see what I mean?

05:59.317 --> 06:02.445
One minute, it's freezing, and the next,
it's like the first day of spring.

06:03.237 --> 06:05.656
The Grand Line
sure lives up to its reputation.

06:06.824 --> 06:08.117
[Usopp] My snow queen!

06:09.243 --> 06:10.161
My masterpiece.

06:14.874 --> 06:16.167
Luffy, look out behind you!

06:17.627 --> 06:18.835
How did she get free?

06:18.836 --> 06:21.296
Your fearlessly incompetent leader.

06:21.297 --> 06:23.465
Luffy, you <i>do</i> know what an assassin is,
don't you?

06:23.466 --> 06:24.509
I do.

06:25.301 --> 06:27.386
I just don't think she wants to hurt us.

06:27.387 --> 06:30.514
Right. And her attacking me was what?
Jealousy of my looks?

06:30.515 --> 06:31.891
[scoffs] You wish.

06:33.643 --> 06:35.936
My gut tells me we can trust her.

06:35.937 --> 06:37.479
And I always trust my gut.

06:37.480 --> 06:39.107
[Mr. 9 chuckles]

06:40.942 --> 06:42.318
Is there something you want to say?

06:43.736 --> 06:46.363
Unlike your insolent crew,

06:46.364 --> 06:48.615
I respect your judgment.

06:48.616 --> 06:51.244
So, can you free me too?

06:55.289 --> 06:57.624
You can't seriously be considering that.

06:57.625 --> 07:01.169
Luffy, it is fine if you trust your gut,
but maybe we keep the assassins tied up

07:01.170 --> 07:03.463
until we figure out
exactly what your gut is telling you?

07:03.464 --> 07:07.217
- Or we can forget we ever met one another.
- Yeah, yeah. Yeah.

07:07.218 --> 07:09.762
And you can just let us go

07:10.263 --> 07:12.348
on that island over there.

07:15.143 --> 07:16.393
[Luffy chuckles]

07:16.394 --> 07:17.395
What?!

07:19.313 --> 07:21.898
It's our very first island
in the Grand Line.

07:21.899 --> 07:24.401
Are those cacti? They're huge.

07:24.402 --> 07:27.112
I don't know,
but that's definitely a town down there.

07:27.113 --> 07:30.031
Thanks for the ride, idiots.

07:30.032 --> 07:31.491
Bye-bye, baby.

07:31.492 --> 07:32.326
Ooh! Ooh!

07:33.411 --> 07:34.494
[water splashes]

07:34.495 --> 07:35.413
[scoffs]

07:37.165 --> 07:38.457
[Usopp gasps]

07:38.458 --> 07:39.709
Oh no.

07:40.877 --> 07:43.087
Well, that's one way
to take care of the problem.

07:44.839 --> 07:46.841
[adventurous music playing]

07:54.974 --> 07:56.976
[foreboding music playing]

08:09.614 --> 08:10.698
[bell tolling]

08:29.175 --> 08:31.219
- [laughs]
- [overlapping chatter]

08:33.596 --> 08:34.930
He seems friendly.

08:34.931 --> 08:36.181
Howdy there.

08:36.182 --> 08:37.934
[upbeat music playing]

08:39.810 --> 08:43.563
Is it me, or is everybody happy to see us?

08:43.564 --> 08:46.400
That's definitely different.

08:47.068 --> 08:47.984
Hi.

08:47.985 --> 08:50.613
Well, they say things are different
in the Grand Line.

08:51.113 --> 08:52.864
Maybe they love pirates here.

08:52.865 --> 08:55.492
I said different, not backwards.

08:55.493 --> 08:58.329
[man] Did I hear you say
that you're pirates?

09:01.707 --> 09:03.125
[Usopp] Luffy, play it cool.

09:04.418 --> 09:05.419
Yeah.

09:07.129 --> 09:11.717
My name is Monkey D. Luffy,
and I'm gonna be King of the Pirates.

09:15.346 --> 09:16.556
Mmm…

09:20.935 --> 09:22.769
[chuckles]

09:22.770 --> 09:24.063
Oh!

09:24.647 --> 09:25.564
Wonderful news!

09:25.565 --> 09:28.108
Here in Whisky Peak,
we simply adore pirates.

09:28.109 --> 09:29.902
Ah! Told ya!

09:30.695 --> 09:32.195
[man and Luffy chuckle]

09:32.196 --> 09:33.114
[man clears throat]

09:34.031 --> 09:36.784
<i>♪ Ma, ma, ma ♪</i>

09:37.285 --> 09:41.746
My name is Igaram,
and I'm the mayor of this humble town.

09:41.747 --> 09:44.249
I would like to extend to you all
our warmest welcome.

09:44.250 --> 09:47.711
I'm sorry. Did you say you love pirates?

09:47.712 --> 09:48.920
Why, of course.

09:48.921 --> 09:51.548
Everyone knows
no one loves tales of adventure

09:51.549 --> 09:53.384
like the people of Whisky Peak.

09:53.884 --> 09:56.886
That and we're one of the first stops
on the Grand Line,

09:56.887 --> 10:00.850
so we found that welcoming pirates
is a lot easier than fighting them.

10:01.767 --> 10:03.226
Actually, that makes sense.

10:03.227 --> 10:08.148
Sister, how blessed are we that we have
yet another pirate crew to entertain.

10:08.149 --> 10:12.819
Well, I hope they're as much fun
as those Tulip Pirates last night.

10:12.820 --> 10:14.779
I promise you, we're way more fun.

10:14.780 --> 10:17.532
Oh. Hmm. [chuckles]

10:17.533 --> 10:21.077
Uh, excuse me.
Are the Tulip Pirates still here?

10:21.078 --> 10:22.370
[Igaram] Oh no. No, no, no.

10:22.371 --> 10:25.332
They came, they partied,
and they continued on,

10:25.333 --> 10:27.084
as most pirate crews do.

10:28.669 --> 10:30.504
Do you also like assassins?

10:31.547 --> 10:33.549
[mysterious music playing]

10:34.258 --> 10:35.509
Why would you ask that?

10:36.093 --> 10:39.639
Because two assassins escaped our ship
and might wash up on this island.

10:40.389 --> 10:44.644
- Guy with a crown, woman with blue hair.
- And you're sure they headed here?

10:47.188 --> 10:49.773
Thank you.
Thank you for warning us, but don't worry.

10:49.774 --> 10:51.900
Just because we don't like
fighting off ne'er-do-wells

10:51.901 --> 10:53.485
doesn't mean we're not capable.

10:53.486 --> 10:54.862
[Nami] Hmm.

10:56.113 --> 10:57.906
E… e… excuse me.

10:57.907 --> 11:01.910
Uh, how long does it take
for a Log Pose to reset on this island?

11:01.911 --> 11:03.703
Oh, the magnetic field should record

11:03.704 --> 11:05.705
and point you
to the closest island by morning.

11:05.706 --> 11:08.124
So we have to stay the whole night?

11:08.125 --> 11:11.169
Oh, I promise you,
it won't be a night you'll soon forget.

11:11.170 --> 11:13.172
[foreboding music playing]

11:14.340 --> 11:17.300
- Okay, let's have a little fun.
- Awesome!

11:17.301 --> 11:18.760
- [chuckles]
- [bell tolling]

11:18.761 --> 11:20.804
What perfect timing.
That's the dinner bell.

11:20.805 --> 11:24.683
Come. I invite you to come and enjoy
the finest Whisky Peak has to offer.

11:24.684 --> 11:26.185
But… but there is a catch.

11:27.395 --> 11:30.898
I insist that you tell us
about your tales of adventure.

11:32.191 --> 11:33.900
Oh. [inhales]

11:33.901 --> 11:35.568
That's not gonna be a problem.

11:35.569 --> 11:37.571
[swanky, upbeat music playing]

12:05.433 --> 12:07.809
All of a sudden,
the beast opens its mouth.

12:07.810 --> 12:11.354
I mean, a mouth so big
it could swallow this entire island.

12:11.355 --> 12:12.647
[patrons gasp]

12:12.648 --> 12:15.525
And then, gulp!
We disappeared into its stomach.

12:15.526 --> 12:16.443
[patrons] Ah.

12:16.444 --> 12:20.155
And then, I had to fight a zombie
to save Sanji's life.

12:20.156 --> 12:22.824
- That's not how it went down.
- That's exactly how it happened.

12:22.825 --> 12:26.411
But then, our captain had a genius idea.

12:26.412 --> 12:28.913
I sang a song and the whale understood,

12:28.914 --> 12:32.167
so he opened his mouth
and gave me back my crew.

12:32.168 --> 12:33.877
[cheering]

12:33.878 --> 12:37.548
<i>♪ Ma, ma, ma ♪</i>

12:38.048 --> 12:40.717
Mmm. A fellow music lover, I see.

12:40.718 --> 12:41.969
Sure am.

12:42.678 --> 12:46.514
You know, I'm still looking
for a musician for our crew.

12:46.515 --> 12:49.268
Yes, a most tempting proposition.

12:49.769 --> 12:52.854
But my responsibilities
lie elsewhere, I'm afraid.

12:52.855 --> 12:56.859
- How about we go for another round?
- Yes, great idea. Another round.

12:58.611 --> 12:59.445
Everyone,

13:00.780 --> 13:03.324
we've come a long way from the East Blue.

13:04.575 --> 13:08.870
Now, we may not know what the rest
of the Grand Line has in store for us,

13:08.871 --> 13:10.122
but we're alive.

13:11.248 --> 13:12.625
And we're together.

13:13.751 --> 13:15.376
So let's celebrate!

13:15.377 --> 13:17.046
[cheering]

13:18.547 --> 13:19.673
Yes!

13:21.175 --> 13:22.258
Yeah!

13:22.259 --> 13:24.677
Yes! Drink! Drink! Drink!

13:24.678 --> 13:26.680
[foreboding music playing]

13:29.266 --> 13:30.518
[Mr. 9 grunts]

13:35.147 --> 13:36.106
[shudders]

13:37.024 --> 13:38.526
I hate wet socks.

13:39.568 --> 13:40.944
[grunts]

13:40.945 --> 13:44.072
And this salt water's
going to do a number on my suit.

13:44.073 --> 13:46.157
Mr. 8 will have our heads for being late.

13:46.158 --> 13:48.202
You know he loathes to be kept waiting.

13:50.037 --> 13:53.582
And I doubt he considers
swallowed by a whale an acceptable excuse.

13:54.083 --> 13:55.835
I'd better find him at once.

13:57.962 --> 13:59.547
[Mr. 9] I'm coming with you.

14:01.423 --> 14:04.552
I can't have you taking all the credit
for our mission.

14:06.762 --> 14:08.555
Or shifting all the blame.

14:08.556 --> 14:10.391
Don't worry.

14:11.016 --> 14:12.351
It wasn't our fault.

14:12.935 --> 14:14.562
I'll tell him you had my back.

14:15.271 --> 14:17.147
- You will?
- [Miss Wednesday] Of course.

14:18.148 --> 14:20.317
We're partners, aren't we?

14:21.610 --> 14:25.321
Besides, I bet those idiotic pirates
have arrived by now.

14:25.322 --> 14:27.741
Including Roronoa Zoro.

14:29.201 --> 14:30.619
I'll make the report.

14:31.161 --> 14:32.830
You tie up loose ends.

14:33.330 --> 14:35.541
Then we'll really be
in Mr. 8's good books.

14:43.215 --> 14:45.217
[upbeat piano music playing]

14:50.890 --> 14:52.098
[waitress] Here we are.

14:52.099 --> 14:54.894
Mmm. You mean that was just the appetizer?

14:55.477 --> 14:57.479
[indistinct chatter]

14:59.189 --> 15:04.444
- You ready to give up yet?
- I'm not even close to drunk.

15:04.445 --> 15:06.530
Yeah, you definitely don't sound it.

15:08.198 --> 15:09.658
Another… [hiccups]

15:10.743 --> 15:11.577
…round.

15:13.913 --> 15:16.373
[patrons chanting] Usopp! Usopp! Usopp!

15:17.374 --> 15:19.460
[cheering]

15:23.047 --> 15:24.423
You know, it's crazy.

15:25.215 --> 15:27.384
I've never even played darts before. Hoo!

15:29.595 --> 15:31.597
[patrons cheering]

15:32.848 --> 15:35.809
I must be
some kind of darts savant! [laughs]

15:36.936 --> 15:38.562
- Give me another.
- [Sanji] It's all on me.

15:39.063 --> 15:40.229
[Zoro] Hey, Chore Boy.

15:40.230 --> 15:42.023
[Sanji] This is good. Try this.

15:42.024 --> 15:44.777
You're looking a bit dry over there.
You want a drink?

15:45.653 --> 15:46.570
Shots?

15:48.489 --> 15:49.615
For you,

15:50.240 --> 15:52.785
the key to a good cocktail

15:53.285 --> 15:54.494
is balance.

15:54.495 --> 15:58.082
Because all of this
means absolutely nothing

15:59.041 --> 16:01.042
if the drink tastes terrible.

16:01.043 --> 16:04.129
But, lucky for you guys,

16:04.922 --> 16:06.090
nobody

16:07.216 --> 16:08.884
is more balanced.

16:09.718 --> 16:12.137
And I call this…

16:18.060 --> 16:18.894
[giggles softly]

16:19.478 --> 16:22.189
…the finest view

16:23.065 --> 16:24.357
in the Grand Line.

16:24.358 --> 16:25.401
[applause]

16:25.985 --> 16:26.986
[chuckles softly]

16:30.823 --> 16:32.199
[snoring]

16:32.825 --> 16:34.951
Don't you feel bad cheating a nun?

16:34.952 --> 16:38.080
There was no cheating.
I outdrank her fair and square.

16:43.711 --> 16:44.919
[sighs]

16:44.920 --> 16:48.256
Now that that fun is over,
I wanna sketch the island.

16:48.257 --> 16:51.676
[gasps] I bet there's a great view
from on top of those cactus mountains.

16:51.677 --> 16:53.553
[nun gags]

16:53.554 --> 16:55.139
Those?

16:55.848 --> 16:58.600
No need to worry yourself with those.

16:59.184 --> 17:00.601
Why not?

17:00.602 --> 17:03.063
They're dangerous.

17:03.564 --> 17:07.192
No reason to go up there. [chuckles]

17:08.819 --> 17:10.153
Um…

17:10.154 --> 17:12.488
Okay, well, now
I'm absolutely going up there.

17:12.489 --> 17:14.323
Yeah, I figured you'd say that.

17:14.324 --> 17:17.828
Sounds like they're hiding something.
Hopefully, it's treasure.

17:18.328 --> 17:19.496
[nun] No!

17:20.080 --> 17:22.666
That money is from the collection plate.

17:23.500 --> 17:25.626
What am I going to tell the congregation?

17:25.627 --> 17:26.545
[Nami] Mmm.

17:27.546 --> 17:29.297
That is your cross to bear, Sister.

17:29.298 --> 17:30.299
[nun groans]

17:31.050 --> 17:32.217
[Usopp] Uh…

17:33.552 --> 17:35.554
[indistinct chatter]

17:42.770 --> 17:43.812
[Luffy sighs]

17:45.314 --> 17:46.774
Look at us, man.

17:47.566 --> 17:49.526
We put together an amazing crew,

17:50.027 --> 17:51.904
made it to the Grand Line,

17:52.488 --> 17:55.324
and now we're one step closer
to our dreams.

17:59.912 --> 18:00.913
What's wrong?

18:02.081 --> 18:02.998
You hungry?

18:08.003 --> 18:09.171
Mihawk.

18:12.007 --> 18:12.841
Hawk Eyes.

18:15.803 --> 18:18.222
I still have a long way to go
to get to his level.

18:24.436 --> 18:26.230
That's what the journey's all about.

18:26.980 --> 18:29.483
You're gonna fight so many tough guys

18:30.067 --> 18:31.735
that by the time you meet him again,

18:32.528 --> 18:33.695
you'll be ready.

18:35.697 --> 18:37.699
I can feel it in my gut.

18:39.451 --> 18:42.746
The same gut that told you
to let that assassin chick go free?

18:43.288 --> 18:46.125
Hey, we still don't know if I was wrong.

18:47.501 --> 18:49.044
[stomach rumbles]

18:51.713 --> 18:52.965
What's it saying now?

18:53.632 --> 18:55.550
That was a dessert grumble.

18:55.551 --> 18:56.552
[Zoro] Hmm.

18:58.178 --> 19:00.681
I think I saw a bakery
on our way into town.

19:02.724 --> 19:03.725
Boom!

19:09.231 --> 19:12.692
So, you two lovely ladies
are sisters, yeah?

19:12.693 --> 19:13.819
- Twins.
- Twins.

19:14.820 --> 19:17.738
Great. And what, uh, can I make for you?

19:17.739 --> 19:19.533
A little desert daiquiri?

19:20.033 --> 19:22.076
East Blue swizzle, perhaps?

19:22.077 --> 19:24.078
Well, we prefer our drinks…

19:24.079 --> 19:25.122
Straight up.

19:27.040 --> 19:28.709
I think I can accommodate that.

19:30.711 --> 19:33.213
Oh, no. We don't drink that swill.

19:33.839 --> 19:36.841
They keep the best bottles
in the lounge upstairs.

19:36.842 --> 19:38.260
Oh, they do?

19:38.760 --> 19:41.930
You seem like a man of discerning taste.

19:42.556 --> 19:44.516
I am. I really, really am.

19:45.017 --> 19:48.144
Well, then perhaps you'd like to…

19:48.145 --> 19:49.479
Sample some?

19:50.689 --> 19:52.399
Uh… uh…

19:53.150 --> 19:54.525
I would like nothing more.

19:54.526 --> 19:56.277
[Usopp laughs]

19:56.278 --> 19:57.195
Bring your friend.

19:57.196 --> 20:00.282
I know we just met,
but it feels like I know you guys.

20:01.074 --> 20:02.033
I will.

20:02.034 --> 20:03.618
[patrons] Oh!

20:03.619 --> 20:06.037
[Usopp laughs]

20:06.038 --> 20:07.622
You're coming with me.

20:07.623 --> 20:08.915
Yeah, no, I'm good here, buddy.

20:08.916 --> 20:13.629
Usopp, when two gorgeous women
ask you to taste their finest,

20:14.254 --> 20:15.464
you taste it.

20:20.344 --> 20:22.178
Well, it… it would be rude not to.

20:22.179 --> 20:23.263
[Sanji] Mm-hmm.

20:23.764 --> 20:24.765
[Luffy] Mmm.

20:26.183 --> 20:27.184
So…

20:28.101 --> 20:28.977
Mmm.

20:29.519 --> 20:31.270
Mmm! Mmm!

20:31.271 --> 20:33.065
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

20:34.149 --> 20:36.026
Apple pie is my favorite.

20:37.236 --> 20:38.486
Mmm.

20:38.487 --> 20:42.032
But… the rhubarb…

20:46.161 --> 20:47.037
Mmm.

20:47.704 --> 20:48.663
Mmm!

20:48.664 --> 20:49.998
Yeah. Nah.

20:51.208 --> 20:52.751
Rhubarb's best.

20:54.211 --> 20:55.420
Although…

20:56.171 --> 20:57.256
Mmm…

20:58.131 --> 21:00.508
[Igaram] I'm partial
to the boysenberry myself.

21:00.509 --> 21:02.552
Equal parts tart and sweet.

21:04.137 --> 21:05.471
Um…

21:05.472 --> 21:07.723
Uh, I'm gonna pay for all of this.

21:07.724 --> 21:09.100
Oh no, please. [chuckles]

21:09.101 --> 21:11.353
No, please. No need for that.

21:12.104 --> 21:14.106
Wow. [chuckles]

21:15.399 --> 21:17.566
You guys are really nice to pirates.

21:17.567 --> 21:20.653
Well, I'd be lying
if I said it wasn't a bit self-serving.

21:20.654 --> 21:26.742
Still, most towns want to kill pirates,
so… thank you for not doing that.

21:26.743 --> 21:29.787
Well, I'm sad to report
that not everyone on the Grand Line

21:29.788 --> 21:31.790
feels the same way that we do.

21:33.000 --> 21:34.042
Oh, no.

21:34.960 --> 21:38.170
Especially for a pirate
with a bounty as high as yours.

21:38.171 --> 21:39.630
You know about my bounty?

21:39.631 --> 21:41.048
Why, of course.

21:41.049 --> 21:42.675
As the first stop on the Grand Line,

21:42.676 --> 21:45.929
we hear all about the happenings
of the various Blues.

21:46.513 --> 21:48.348
Now, if you don't mind me asking,

21:48.849 --> 21:52.602
how does a pirate of such a young age
acquire a bounty of that magnitude?

21:53.603 --> 21:54.980
[sighs] Well,

21:56.189 --> 21:58.025
there was this Marine that we took down.

21:58.525 --> 22:01.153
Then this really evil butler.

22:01.862 --> 22:05.574
And then this fishman
holding Nami's entire village hostage.

22:07.993 --> 22:10.662
Sounds like you… help people.

22:12.247 --> 22:13.373
I do?

22:15.500 --> 22:17.544
If I can offer one word of advice,

22:18.420 --> 22:19.629
careful who you trust.

22:20.213 --> 22:22.424
The Grand Line is a dangerous place.

22:23.050 --> 22:23.884
[Luffy] Mmm.

22:24.676 --> 22:26.511
My gut is not just for pies.

22:27.804 --> 22:30.390
It tells me who to trust. Like you.

22:31.516 --> 22:33.310
I can tell you're a good person.

22:34.061 --> 22:35.812
Or that assassin lady.

22:38.482 --> 22:40.691
- Miss Wednesday.
- Yeah.

22:40.692 --> 22:42.193
Yeah, that's her name.

22:42.194 --> 22:44.112
[footsteps approaching]

22:50.952 --> 22:52.495
[Igaram] I did warn you.

22:52.496 --> 22:54.623
Be careful who you trust.

22:56.333 --> 22:59.336
- [chilling saxophone music playing]
- [skull screaming]

23:03.799 --> 23:05.926
Enchanting Vertigo Dance.

23:16.311 --> 23:18.730
[distorted] Enchanting Vertigo Dance.

23:20.649 --> 23:21.650
[chuckles]

23:38.917 --> 23:40.919
[Miss Wednesday panting]

23:41.711 --> 23:43.296
[Luffy snoring]

23:45.215 --> 23:46.757
I was beginning to worry.

23:46.758 --> 23:48.342
The mission was a success.

23:48.343 --> 23:50.345
[mysterious music playing]

23:56.852 --> 23:59.354
[whistling]

24:09.364 --> 24:12.408
[whistling continues]

24:12.409 --> 24:15.078
[man sighs]

24:27.132 --> 24:29.134
[flies buzzing]

24:39.227 --> 24:40.854
The Tulip Pirates.

24:41.563 --> 24:44.191
[man] You weren't supposed to see that.

24:47.736 --> 24:48.945
[groans]

24:49.696 --> 24:52.240
I should have known
this town was too good to be true.

24:52.741 --> 24:55.285
You don't love pirates. You kill them.

24:56.286 --> 24:58.788
We allow them to be who they really are.

24:59.748 --> 25:03.835
<i>Drunken, lecherous rogues.</i>

25:05.545 --> 25:07.672
<i>And then we take advantage of that.</i>

25:11.510 --> 25:13.803
<i>But we're not completely heartless.</i>

25:15.305 --> 25:16.973
<i>We always give them</i>

25:18.433 --> 25:19.768
<i>a proper burial</i>

25:21.144 --> 25:23.146
<i>when we're done with them.</i>

25:25.440 --> 25:27.484
Don't worry, girlie. [chuckles]

25:30.904 --> 25:33.406
We'll take care of you too.

25:33.907 --> 25:35.408
[grunting]

25:46.962 --> 25:48.129
[sighs]

25:48.713 --> 25:50.005
[urinating]

25:50.006 --> 25:51.800
[sighs]

25:55.428 --> 25:57.430
[suspenseful music playing]

25:59.057 --> 26:02.310
The least you could do
is buy me a drink first.

26:03.562 --> 26:04.437
[pulls zipper]

26:05.021 --> 26:06.730
[tense action music playing]

26:06.731 --> 26:08.358
[grunting]

26:12.404 --> 26:14.906
Zoro, this place is a… trap.

26:15.490 --> 26:16.574
[sighs]

26:16.575 --> 26:17.825
Yeah, I kind of got that.

26:17.826 --> 26:19.327
I thought you were drunk.

26:20.328 --> 26:21.287
So did they.

26:21.288 --> 26:23.038
Where are the others?
Gotta get out of here.

26:23.039 --> 26:26.250
Luffy went to find a bakery.
Usopp and the cook are still inside.

26:26.251 --> 26:29.879
Okay. You get them. I'll find Luffy.
We'll meet back at the Merry.

26:31.298 --> 26:32.757
Watch out in there.

26:33.300 --> 26:34.800
I'll be careful.

26:34.801 --> 26:36.093
[grunting]

26:36.094 --> 26:37.721
[clamoring]

26:40.682 --> 26:42.559
Gonna need more than two to take me down.

26:43.977 --> 26:44.936
[grunts]

26:45.645 --> 26:47.355
[grunting]

26:53.111 --> 26:55.739
[slow clapping]

27:01.161 --> 27:02.621
Quite an entrance.

27:03.413 --> 27:06.915
Unfortunately, what you failed
to understand is--

27:06.916 --> 27:08.585
You're all Baroque Works.

27:09.085 --> 27:12.171
And this whole town is a ruse
to get pirates drunk and kill them?

27:12.172 --> 27:13.214
[chuckles]

27:14.549 --> 27:16.593
We also steal their loot.

27:18.261 --> 27:19.553
For your costume budget?

27:19.554 --> 27:21.639
For Baroque Works!

27:21.640 --> 27:23.724
[crowd cheers and whistles]

27:23.725 --> 27:28.312
The man before you
felled our dearly departed Mr. 7.

27:28.313 --> 27:31.149
A stroke of dumb luck, no doubt.

27:31.650 --> 27:35.819
But I have it on good authority

27:35.820 --> 27:39.782
that whoever kills Roronoa Zoro

27:39.783 --> 27:43.786
will be fast-tracked to frontier agent!

27:43.787 --> 27:45.705
[crowd cheers]

27:46.373 --> 27:47.749
[suspenseful music playing]

27:53.505 --> 27:55.589
[Mr. 9] There are a hundred of us

27:55.590 --> 27:58.551
and only one of you.

28:03.890 --> 28:05.308
I like our odds.

28:07.519 --> 28:08.853
[men grunt]

28:17.153 --> 28:20.114
This will be a great workout
for my new swords.

28:20.115 --> 28:21.657
Now!

28:21.658 --> 28:22.784
[all yelling]

28:23.535 --> 28:25.619
[grunting]

28:25.620 --> 28:27.622
[tense action music playing]

28:44.055 --> 28:45.014
[thud]

28:47.100 --> 28:49.102
[grunting]

29:04.242 --> 29:05.285
[Zoro] Hmm.

29:06.870 --> 29:08.120
- Good sword.
- [Mr. 9] Come on!

29:08.121 --> 29:09.121
[yells]

29:09.122 --> 29:11.124
[grunting]

29:20.884 --> 29:22.259
[yells]

29:22.260 --> 29:23.136
[grunts]

29:30.852 --> 29:33.646
- [man yells]
- [man 2 grunts]

29:34.689 --> 29:35.606
[yells]

29:35.607 --> 29:37.525
[grunting]

29:58.755 --> 29:59.881
Please!

30:02.717 --> 30:06.596
- I'm a woman of the cloth.
- How many nuns does a fake town need?

30:07.514 --> 30:08.473
[Zoro grunts]

30:11.017 --> 30:12.434
[both grunt]

30:12.435 --> 30:13.812
[Zoro grunts]

30:18.566 --> 30:19.442
[grunts]

30:33.623 --> 30:34.958
[nun screams]

30:37.085 --> 30:38.670
[grunts]

30:49.973 --> 30:52.183
I do hope you've saved your strength.

30:52.684 --> 30:53.684
One hundred agents

30:53.685 --> 30:56.354
and, by my count,
you've only taken out 40.

30:57.564 --> 30:59.566
[soft flamenco music playing]

31:03.403 --> 31:07.489
You'll never surpass me and Yoru
if you don't learn to use your new blades.

31:07.490 --> 31:10.118
I'll shatter them like I did before.

31:23.590 --> 31:25.592
[men yell]

31:27.552 --> 31:28.720
Forty-four.

31:31.014 --> 31:33.182
[tense action music playing]

31:36.686 --> 31:37.687
[grunting]

31:38.730 --> 31:39.730
Fifty.

31:39.731 --> 31:41.566
[men yelling]

31:42.859 --> 31:44.777
[grunting]

32:19.896 --> 32:21.272
Sixty-three.

32:22.732 --> 32:25.525
[Igaram] You should've taken this
straight to your father.

32:25.526 --> 32:27.986
[Miss Wednesday] We started this.
We'll finish it together.

32:27.987 --> 32:29.821
We need to find a way off this island.

32:29.822 --> 32:32.324
Those pirates have a ship.
Mr. 9 will keep them occupied.

32:32.325 --> 32:34.117
[Igaram] You want us
to steal their vessel?

32:34.118 --> 32:37.914
[Miss Wednesday] What choice do we have?
Getting home is all that matters.

32:41.584 --> 32:42.710
You.

32:43.252 --> 32:45.046
I thought you were a good guy,

32:45.546 --> 32:47.673
but you're in cahoots with her.

32:47.674 --> 32:48.632
And you!

32:48.633 --> 32:50.468
I thought you were good too.

32:50.969 --> 32:54.262
But I won't let you
steal our ship! [grunts]

32:54.263 --> 32:57.058
- We don't have time for this!
- [Luffy yells, grunts]

32:57.725 --> 32:58.893
[Miss Wednesday gasps]

33:00.812 --> 33:01.770
[Luffy] Huh?

33:01.771 --> 33:03.146
[suspenseful music playing]

33:03.147 --> 33:03.982
[grunts]

33:10.321 --> 33:11.698
[Luffy] Hey! Get back here!

33:13.116 --> 33:13.992
[grunts]

33:14.701 --> 33:15.660
Aah!

33:17.412 --> 33:19.872
Someone ought to knock that crown
off your head.

33:20.707 --> 33:22.083
I feel like that someone's me.

33:23.084 --> 33:25.627
What the hell are you doing? Kill him!

33:25.628 --> 33:27.296
[tense action music playing]

33:29.465 --> 33:31.467
[grunting]

34:02.957 --> 34:03.791
Seventy-two.

34:13.801 --> 34:15.344
[music fades]

34:17.805 --> 34:18.890
[bones crack]

34:20.600 --> 34:21.683
[chuckles]

34:21.684 --> 34:22.726
[yells]

34:22.727 --> 34:24.520
[grunting]

34:25.104 --> 34:26.898
[tense action music playing]

34:27.940 --> 34:30.193
[grunting]

34:31.444 --> 34:32.278
[grunts]

34:32.779 --> 34:33.780
[grunts]

34:34.447 --> 34:36.574
[grunting]

34:53.966 --> 34:55.342
[Usopp gasps]

34:55.343 --> 34:56.469
Zoro!

34:57.053 --> 34:58.429
Help us.

35:03.601 --> 35:05.978
[grunting]

35:07.897 --> 35:08.773
Ah.

35:11.067 --> 35:11.943
Seventy-seven.

35:12.443 --> 35:13.985
[screams]

35:13.986 --> 35:15.780
- [gasps]
- Ooh.

35:16.823 --> 35:18.825
[grunting]

35:20.201 --> 35:21.077
Seventy-eight.

35:21.577 --> 35:22.744
[grunts]

35:22.745 --> 35:25.748
Get the ship ready to sail.
We'll meet you onboard.

35:26.374 --> 35:29.252
Hey, mosshead! Are you gonna free us?

35:35.341 --> 35:37.135
You're good with a knife, right?

35:38.344 --> 35:41.639
- [Usopp] I'm getting it. I'm getting it.
- [Sanji] Stop! I got it!

35:42.390 --> 35:43.432
[yells]

35:43.933 --> 35:45.810
[grunts]

35:49.981 --> 35:51.983
[grunting]

36:01.742 --> 36:03.661
[groans]

36:04.453 --> 36:05.705
[yells]

36:08.624 --> 36:12.170
[grunting]

36:20.136 --> 36:21.596
[screams]

36:23.931 --> 36:26.016
[tense action music continues]

36:26.017 --> 36:28.019
[grunting]

36:44.660 --> 36:46.037
Aah!

36:50.124 --> 36:51.417
Eighty-five.

36:55.588 --> 36:57.590
[suspenseful music playing]

37:02.094 --> 37:05.056
What are you waiting for? A formal invite?

37:06.057 --> 37:08.058
[tense action music continues]

37:08.059 --> 37:09.810
[grunting]

37:22.949 --> 37:23.991
[man groans]

37:26.118 --> 37:27.495
Ninety-two.

37:40.800 --> 37:42.802
[suspenseful music playing]

37:43.678 --> 37:44.719
Aah!

37:44.720 --> 37:47.348
[grunting]

37:52.019 --> 37:52.936
Nami!

37:52.937 --> 37:53.938
Luffy?

37:59.360 --> 38:00.736
[grunts]

38:01.570 --> 38:03.155
- [grunts]
- [all scream]

38:05.825 --> 38:07.492
[Luffy coughing]

38:07.493 --> 38:09.745
[Miss Wednesday and Igaram grunting]

38:11.163 --> 38:12.289
[Igaram coughs]

38:12.290 --> 38:15.292
- [Luffy] They're both Baroque Works.
- This entire town is Baroque Works.

38:15.293 --> 38:17.502
There's more going on here
than you could possibly know.

38:17.503 --> 38:20.463
We know your powder-wigged friend
led us into a trap.

38:20.464 --> 38:22.091
And you're trying to steal the Merry.

38:22.591 --> 38:24.134
They're trying to steal the Merry.

38:24.135 --> 38:27.596
Look, I'm sorry it has to be this way.
We're only doing what we must.

38:29.098 --> 38:30.348
[grunts softly]

38:30.349 --> 38:32.601
[mysterious music playing]

38:36.397 --> 38:38.232
- I…
- [woman laughing]

38:42.111 --> 38:45.363
Look who we have here, Mr. 5.

38:45.364 --> 38:48.576
A couple of walking corpses,
Miss Valentine.

38:50.953 --> 38:53.748
[skulls screaming]

38:55.458 --> 38:58.251
If Mr. Zero sent you,
you can tell him we don't need backup.

38:58.252 --> 38:59.795
Oh, baby girl.

39:00.296 --> 39:01.756
Mr. Zero sent us,

39:02.506 --> 39:03.840
but we're not your backup.

39:03.841 --> 39:06.343
Did you think
we wouldn't find out who you really are?

39:06.344 --> 39:08.636
Hey, I've been honest
about being a pirate.

39:08.637 --> 39:12.808
Someone's been poking their nose
into our organization's secrets.

39:14.226 --> 39:16.354
Luffy, I don't think they're after us.

39:23.027 --> 39:24.403
Bomb Bomb Fruit!

39:25.112 --> 39:28.698
Nose Fancy Cannon!

39:28.699 --> 39:30.618
- [Igaram] Run!
- [Nami gasps]

39:35.039 --> 39:36.414
That guy has booger bombs?

39:36.415 --> 39:38.750
[Nami pants] Where did the other one go?

39:38.751 --> 39:40.502
Miss Valentine's Kilo Kilo powers
allow her

39:40.503 --> 39:43.296
to change her body weight at will,
which means…

39:43.297 --> 39:45.383
- [wind whistling]
- [Miss Valentine chuckles]

39:45.966 --> 39:46.884
[Nami] Oh shit.

39:51.222 --> 39:54.016
- [grunts]
- Go, go, go, go. This way! This way!

39:59.605 --> 40:01.399
It's more fun when they run.

40:06.153 --> 40:08.155
[suspenseful music playing]

40:13.160 --> 40:16.497
[whistling in background]

40:20.876 --> 40:23.504
[whistling continues]

40:25.923 --> 40:27.048
[sighs]

40:27.049 --> 40:27.925
Just give up.

40:29.427 --> 40:32.513
You bested a bunch of peons.

40:34.557 --> 40:38.644
Now you must face my elite guards.

40:40.771 --> 40:41.688
[sighs]

40:41.689 --> 40:43.190
[foreboding music playing]

40:59.623 --> 41:01.291
[Mr. 9] Attack!

41:01.292 --> 41:03.043
[guards yell]

41:07.173 --> 41:09.508
[mystical whirring]

41:11.427 --> 41:13.012
[suspenseful music playing]

41:24.356 --> 41:25.608
Time to take that crown.

41:28.110 --> 41:30.695
[yells]

41:30.696 --> 41:32.948
[tense action music playing]

41:33.532 --> 41:34.991
[laughs]

41:34.992 --> 41:36.785
[grunting]

41:57.473 --> 41:58.766
[whimpers]

42:02.937 --> 42:04.939
[woman] Time to repent.

42:07.983 --> 42:09.442
[hymnal music playing in Latin]

42:09.443 --> 42:10.569
[Mr. 9 chuckles]

42:12.029 --> 42:14.156
<i>♪ Amen ♪</i>

42:14.823 --> 42:18.494
<i>♪ Amen ♪</i>

42:19.870 --> 42:21.205
[skull screams]

42:21.705 --> 42:23.707
[Miss Monday grunting]

42:31.966 --> 42:33.968
[panting]

42:35.135 --> 42:37.137
[Miss Monday grunting]

42:40.015 --> 42:44.103
Home Run Hide-a-Bat!

42:45.854 --> 42:46.897
[cackles]

42:49.066 --> 42:50.609
- [Zoro grunts]
- [laughs]

43:01.120 --> 43:03.122
[Zoro grunting]

43:05.874 --> 43:06.875
[Miss Monday grunts]

43:10.254 --> 43:11.463
[grunts]

43:16.385 --> 43:17.428
[Mr. 5] Come on out.

43:18.512 --> 43:20.388
All we want is a civil conversation.

43:20.389 --> 43:24.852
We promise it'll only hurt…
a little. [chuckles]

43:28.897 --> 43:29.898
[imitates kissing]

43:32.568 --> 43:33.944
- [Luffy huffs]
- [Nami] Luffy!

43:34.653 --> 43:36.446
- [whispering] What?
- No.

43:36.447 --> 43:38.324
[Mr. 5] It's a damn shame, Miss Valentine.

43:38.949 --> 43:41.534
Mr. Zero thought
she showed a lot of promise.

43:41.535 --> 43:44.371
But I guess
she never really was one of us.

43:45.205 --> 43:47.915
Were ya, Miss Wednesday?

43:47.916 --> 43:50.711
Or should we call you, "Your Highness"?

43:52.463 --> 43:53.463
[gasps]

43:53.464 --> 43:55.174
[suspenseful music swelling]

43:57.092 --> 43:58.093
Move!

44:06.018 --> 44:10.063
Hear that?
Those are officer agents down there.

44:10.064 --> 44:12.065
Even higher than me.

44:12.066 --> 44:16.486
Which means your friends
are as good as dead.

44:16.487 --> 44:17.488
[sighs]

44:19.031 --> 44:21.491
Some crew you all turned out to be.

44:21.492 --> 44:25.536
Can't even make it
past your first island in the Grand Line.

44:25.537 --> 44:27.289
[laughs]

44:30.042 --> 44:31.043
[exhales sharply]

44:32.961 --> 44:34.755
[tense action music playing]

44:42.179 --> 44:44.055
[Mr. 9 screams]

44:44.056 --> 44:45.057
[Miss Monday grunts]

44:47.142 --> 44:47.976
[grunts]

44:49.645 --> 44:50.813
Ninety-eight.

44:52.356 --> 44:53.607
Ninety-nine.

45:03.450 --> 45:04.534
[grunts]

45:04.535 --> 45:05.619
[groans]

45:08.622 --> 45:09.623
[exhales sharply]

45:11.875 --> 45:12.875
A hundred.

45:12.876 --> 45:15.254
[mysterious music playing]

45:16.338 --> 45:18.674
Don't be too proud of yourself.

45:27.224 --> 45:28.434
It's a start.

45:29.309 --> 45:30.561
Barely.

45:38.902 --> 45:40.237
[Nami] Are you okay, Luffy?

45:43.449 --> 45:44.658
[Luffy] Where are they?

45:45.451 --> 45:46.868
[Igaram] Get to the shore.

45:46.869 --> 45:48.787
[Nami] With those two out there?
It's suicide.

45:50.038 --> 45:53.333
Now's a great time for you
to explain yourself, Your Highness.

45:54.293 --> 45:57.378
Igaram and I went undercover
in Baroque Works to bring them down.

45:57.379 --> 45:59.088
That's why they're after us.

45:59.089 --> 46:01.382
And why are we supposed
to believe that story?

46:01.383 --> 46:03.676
It doesn't matter if you believe us.

46:03.677 --> 46:06.304
If we don't get out of here,
we're all dead.

46:06.305 --> 46:07.598
[Igaram grunts]

46:10.851 --> 46:12.018
Oh.

46:12.019 --> 46:13.603
[somber music playing]

46:13.604 --> 46:15.439
- What's up?
- Nah, it's nothing.

46:21.361 --> 46:22.571
Oh no.

46:23.155 --> 46:24.239
[Igaram] Yeah.

46:28.410 --> 46:31.996
- [Miss Wednesday] Oh. Oh.
- [grunting]

46:31.997 --> 46:33.498
- Oh, oh, oh.
- [Igaram groans]

46:33.499 --> 46:34.833
[coughs]

46:38.712 --> 46:40.839
Listen. Listen to me.

46:41.548 --> 46:42.925
I won't make it to the ship.

46:43.509 --> 46:45.010
- But you must.
- No.

46:46.804 --> 46:48.555
We've been through too much.

46:49.139 --> 46:51.141
This is not how it ends.

46:54.520 --> 46:55.521
[grunts]

47:01.276 --> 47:02.694
[weeping]

47:06.365 --> 47:07.449
[grunts]

47:09.034 --> 47:10.077
I am Igaram,

47:10.702 --> 47:12.746
Captain of the Alabasta Royal Guard.

47:13.247 --> 47:17.167
You must take my princess to safety.
The future of our country depends on it.

47:20.295 --> 47:21.796
I give you my word.

47:21.797 --> 47:23.256
Luffy, how can you promise that?

47:23.257 --> 47:25.466
We don't know
what kind of danger they're involved in.

47:25.467 --> 47:26.426
Nami.

47:33.475 --> 47:34.643
One billion berry.

47:35.727 --> 47:38.689
- What?
- Our fee for saving your princess, Chief.

47:40.607 --> 47:42.901
- [Zoro] Always negotiating.
- Zoro!

47:43.569 --> 47:46.363
- What the hell's going on here?
- Catch you up later.

47:46.905 --> 47:49.323
Got a job. We need to get her out of here.

47:49.324 --> 47:52.995
Don't drag me
into one of your money-making schemes.

47:56.790 --> 48:00.669
Listen, I'll hold them off as long as
you need to get to the ship and cast off.

48:01.169 --> 48:03.838
- We'll help you.
- No, no, no. Her safety is the priority.

48:03.839 --> 48:06.257
The only way to ensure that
is for you three to take her,

48:06.258 --> 48:09.469
get to your vessel,
and leave this place immediately.

48:11.346 --> 48:13.514
I can't do this without you.

48:13.515 --> 48:14.599
[Igaram] Nonsense.

48:14.600 --> 48:15.684
Listen to me.

48:16.184 --> 48:18.478
You're the only one
that can save our kingdom now.

48:19.479 --> 48:22.858
Now, I'm gonna give you cover,
then you run.

48:24.776 --> 48:26.737
- You must remember…
- Don't worry.

48:28.322 --> 48:29.531
We will protect her.

48:34.661 --> 48:36.663
[Miss Wednesday weeps]

48:37.164 --> 48:38.206
[Igaram] Now go.

48:41.543 --> 48:43.545
[suspenseful music playing]

48:56.642 --> 48:58.435
[Mr. 5] You can surrender if you want.

48:59.186 --> 49:00.479
Won't make a difference.

49:00.979 --> 49:03.941
You're dying right here,
in your little fake town.

49:04.441 --> 49:06.443
You know Baroque Works policy.

49:07.027 --> 49:09.071
No traitors left alive.

49:12.115 --> 49:13.116
[Mr. 5 laughs]

49:14.201 --> 49:15.786
What's with the tie, Mr. 8?

49:16.370 --> 49:17.787
Not exactly drippy.

49:17.788 --> 49:19.790
Want to look good to meet your maker?

49:24.127 --> 49:25.337
Not quite.

49:28.090 --> 49:31.092
<i>♪ Ma, ma, ma! ♪</i>

49:31.093 --> 49:31.969
Aah!

49:34.596 --> 49:37.265
<i>♪ Yeah! ♪</i>

49:38.058 --> 49:40.852
<i>♪ Ah ♪</i>

49:43.480 --> 49:44.773
Where is everyone?

49:45.732 --> 49:47.734
Come on. We gotta get after 'em.

49:48.235 --> 49:50.278
There you are. What the hell is going on?

49:50.779 --> 49:52.154
Cast off. Now.

49:52.155 --> 49:53.698
[Usopp] Whoa! What's she doing here?

49:53.699 --> 49:55.784
[Nami] I'll explain later.
We need to leave.

50:03.625 --> 50:05.002
[music fades out]

50:06.628 --> 50:08.630
[wind whistling]

50:13.260 --> 50:15.470
- Hello.
- [Igaram grunts]

50:16.888 --> 50:18.472
Is that all you've got?

50:18.473 --> 50:20.392
[Mr. 5] Enough fooling around.

50:21.018 --> 50:23.519
Time to dispose of this joker.

50:23.520 --> 50:25.522
[mysterious music playing]

50:43.999 --> 50:46.918
[inaudible]

51:00.599 --> 51:01.516
It's okay.

51:02.184 --> 51:04.435
[Miss Wednesday sobbing]

51:04.436 --> 51:05.645
We've got you.

51:07.939 --> 51:09.941
[music fades out]

51:33.799 --> 51:34.716
Gross.

51:35.217 --> 51:36.551
And embarrassing.

51:37.844 --> 51:39.513
One hundred agents down.

51:40.472 --> 51:41.931
One hell of a mess.

51:41.932 --> 51:42.974
[liquid splashes]

51:44.684 --> 51:46.311
Well, lookee here.

51:47.395 --> 51:48.980
- We've got a live one.
- [coughs]

51:54.194 --> 51:55.237
[Mr. 5] Well,

51:56.988 --> 51:58.698
looks like you got your ass beat.

52:01.159 --> 52:05.455
The woman you knew as Miss Wednesday
is a spy and a traitor.

52:05.956 --> 52:09.167
Turns out she was
Alabasta's missing princess all along.

52:09.960 --> 52:11.001
Help us find her.

52:11.002 --> 52:13.421
And you get your revenge.

52:14.631 --> 52:17.134
And why should I tell you anything?

52:22.931 --> 52:25.600
Because the full wrath of Baroque Works

52:26.309 --> 52:29.312
is about to rain down
on her pretty little head.

52:30.397 --> 52:32.566
If you don't help us,
the same thing will happen to you.

52:33.400 --> 52:34.442
Hmm.

52:37.946 --> 52:39.573
She may be a traitor,

52:40.657 --> 52:43.660
but she's still my partner.

52:44.661 --> 52:46.454
I'll never betray her.

52:47.205 --> 52:48.206
[Miss Valentine] Hmm.

52:49.499 --> 52:52.627
I seriously can't imagine
anything more demented.

52:54.254 --> 52:56.673
Because you're kind of cute,

52:57.716 --> 53:00.217
I'll give you one last chance.

53:00.218 --> 53:02.429
Now, if you don't talk…

53:04.723 --> 53:08.101
I'm going to take
my incredibly stylish little shoe

53:08.602 --> 53:12.063
and bring it down
on that smug little face.

53:12.689 --> 53:13.606
[Mr. 9 chuckles]

53:13.607 --> 53:19.070
And you better believe
I will enjoy every second of it.

53:20.614 --> 53:23.074
So, what do you say?

53:25.410 --> 53:28.330
[laughs]

53:30.832 --> 53:31.750
[sighs]

53:32.834 --> 53:34.169
I say

53:34.753 --> 53:38.089
Mr. Zero sent you both to stop my partner,

53:38.590 --> 53:39.799
but she got away,

53:40.300 --> 53:43.178
which means <i>you</i> failed.

53:44.054 --> 53:48.183
And we all know
Mr. Zero doesn't tolerate failure.

53:49.267 --> 53:54.689
I bet he's dispatching the Unluckies
as we speak.

53:58.860 --> 53:59.986
Ah.

54:02.656 --> 54:04.741
So you can kill me if you want.

54:06.284 --> 54:09.204
But you're both already dead.

54:09.788 --> 54:12.165
- [Mr. 5 grunts]
- [Mr. 9 laughs]

54:13.583 --> 54:16.002
Bye-bye, baby.

54:17.254 --> 54:18.129
Buh-bye.

54:24.594 --> 54:26.512
[Sanji] Look, I thought
we had a real connection

54:26.513 --> 54:28.013
before she pulled the knife out.

54:28.014 --> 54:30.599
I think I'm never following you
anywhere ever again.

54:30.600 --> 54:32.768
You can say whatever you want.
She was interested.

54:32.769 --> 54:35.105
Yes. In stabbing you.

54:37.524 --> 54:38.525
[Zoro clears throat]

54:42.404 --> 54:43.405
So,

54:44.322 --> 54:45.532
you got your fight?

54:46.825 --> 54:47.784
I did.

54:50.203 --> 54:52.872
Did you figure out
what your gut was telling you about her?

54:53.498 --> 54:54.708
She needed help.

55:00.005 --> 55:02.007
[mysterious music playing]

55:17.814 --> 55:19.607
I won't let you down.

55:45.842 --> 55:49.095
My name is Nefertari Vivi,

55:49.804 --> 55:51.681
Princess of Alabasta.

55:53.266 --> 55:56.895
Baroque Works has been sowing dissent
between my father and our citizens,

55:57.812 --> 56:00.898
putting my country
on the verge of civil war.

56:00.899 --> 56:02.275
To what end?

56:03.568 --> 56:04.861
I do not know.

56:06.112 --> 56:09.406
Igaram and I discovered the one thing

56:09.407 --> 56:14.788
that may put an end to Baroque Works's
machinations and save my kingdom,

56:15.747 --> 56:18.583
the true identity of their leader,

56:19.292 --> 56:20.502
Mr. Zero.

56:21.795 --> 56:25.423
I must get this information to my father,
the king, immediately.

56:32.138 --> 56:33.515
[Nami] More weird weather?

56:36.059 --> 56:37.060
No.

56:37.685 --> 56:39.979
- This is--
- [woman] Quite the ship you have here.

56:41.356 --> 56:43.650
[foreboding music playing]

56:44.692 --> 56:45.652
[gasps]

56:52.534 --> 56:54.536
["Whisky Peak Saloon" playing]

57:21.354 --> 57:28.277
<i>♪ Whisky Peak Saloon ♪</i>

57:28.278 --> 57:31.573
<i>♪ Whisky Peak ♪</i>

57:32.073 --> 57:35.034
<i>♪ Whisky Peak Saloon ♪</i>

57:35.660 --> 57:38.871
<i>♪ Whisky Peak Saloon ♪</i>

57:38.872 --> 57:40.747
<i>♪ Whisky Peak ♪</i>

57:40.748 --> 57:44.711
<i>♪ Whisky Peak Saloon ♪</i>

58:20.038 --> 58:26.919
<i>♪ Whisky Peak Saloon ♪</i>

58:26.920 --> 58:30.423
<i>♪ Whisky Peak, Whisky Peak ♪</i>

58:30.924 --> 58:37.513
<i>♪ Whisky Peak Saloon ♪</i>

58:37.514 --> 58:39.515
<i>♪ Whisky Peak ♪</i>

